[WHO's influenza update is available at https://www.who.int/influenza/surveillance_monitoring/updates/2020_08_17_surveillance_update_374.pdf.

For more on the US FDA COVID-19 combination diagnostic test see https://www.fda.gov/news-events/press-announcements/coronavirus-covid-19-update-fda-authorizes-additional-covid-19-combination-diagnostic-test-ahead-flu.

For recommendations for seasonal influenza vaccination and antiviral use in EU, including for children and adolescents, see https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/sites/default/files/documents/seasonal-influenza-antiviral-use-2018.pdf.

The solution to early detection of single or multiple pathogen infections lies in implementing robust indicator based and/or sentinel surveillance supported by reliable and quality laboratory testing so that disease trends and impending surges/outbreaks can be effectively monitored. - Mod.UBA]

